Attribution Notice
==================

This work is an adaptation of the MATLAB reference implementation accompanying:

    Zheng, G., Horstmeyer, R., & Yang, C. (2020).
    "On a universal solution to the transport-of-intensity equation."
    Optics Letters, 45(7), 1607–1610.
    https://arxiv.org/abs/1912.07371

The original MATLAB code was released by the authors under the Creative Commons
Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY 4.0).
The original source code is available at: https://arxiv.org/abs/1912.07371

Changes made in this adaptation
--------------------------------

- The MATLAB source code was translated into Python by Way Science Lab (2026).
- The implementation was restructured as an installable Python package
  (US_TIE_Zhang_et_al_2020_py), with a modular architecture separating the Poisson solvers,
  iterative solver, propagation methods, and user-facing pipeline.
- A DCT-based Neumann boundary-condition Poisson solver was added, along with
  a self-consistent finite-difference forward model, extending the original
  FFT-only implementation.
- Comprehensive documentation was written, including inline docstrings, a
  Sphinx documentation site, and a plain-language README aimed at a general
  scientific audience.
- A full test suite (68 tests) was written to verify correctness of all
  components.

Use of AI assistance
---------------------

This adaptation — including the Python translation, software architecture,
test suite, and documentation — was produced with the assistance of Claude
(claude.ai), an AI assistant made by Anthropic. All generated code and
documentation was reviewed by Way Science Lab.

